      "instruction": {
        "type": "prompt",
        "text": "Ask about preferred days and times.\n\nSay something like: \"What days and times work best for you?\"\n\nIf they give a vague answer like \"anytime\" or \"whenever\", \nnarrow it down: \"Great — so mornings and afternoons both \nwork? Weekdays, weekends, or either?\"\n\nIf they give a specific time like \"Tuesday at 2pm\", \nacknowledge it: \"Got it — we'll do our best to get you \nin around that time.\"\n\nIf the user refuses to answer or says \"just pick something\":\nExplain why it matters: \"I hear you — the reason I ask is so \nwe don't book you at a time that doesn't work and you'd have \nto reschedule. Even a general preference like 'mornings' or \n'after 3pm' helps a lot. Anything come to mind?\"\n\nDo NOT ask more than twice."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Fallback node",
      "edges": [
        {
          "destination_node_id": "node-1772591837593",
          "id": "edge-1772573251738-0-ndcrb413g",
          "transition_condition": {
            "type": "prompt",
            "prompt": "User wants to be transferred to a real person or front desk"
          }
        },
        {
          "destination_node_id": "node-1772591755370",
          "id": "node-1772573251738-edge-1772574933845-g3fhyodbm",
          "transition_condition": {
            "type": "prompt",
            "prompt": "User wants to end the call or call back later\n"
          }
        },
        {
          "destination_node_id": "node-1772568303095",
          "id": "node-1772573251738-edge-1772591674741-ijg0lkk40",
          "transition_condition": {
            "type": "prompt",
            "prompt": "User changed their mind and wants to continue providing info\tGo "
          }
        }
      ],
      "id": "node-1772573251738",
      "type": "conversation",
      "display_position": {
        "x": -1789.6714395343936,
        "y": 841.5661552806184
      },
      "instruction": {
        "type": "prompt",
        "text": "The user has declined to provide scheduling information for when they would like to be contacted.\n\nAcknowledge their concern warmly, then explain: \"I completely \nunderstand, and I don't want to push you on anything you're \nnot comfortable with. The thing is, the clinic does need all \nof these details to get your appointment set up properly.\"\n\nThen offer three options:\n1. Transfer: \"If you'd prefer, I can connect you with someone \n   at the front desk who can help directly.\"\n2. End: \"Otherwise, you're always welcome to call us back when you're ready — we'll be here!\"\n\nWait for the user to choose."
      }
    },
